  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Rationale\r\nHaving pinned dependencies for the tools helps in reliability and reduces the attack vector https://github.com/ossf/scorecard/blob/main/docs/checks.md#pinned-dependencies\r\n\r\nThe [Makefile](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/Makefile) install dev tools without it being as pinned SHA.\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/4d88974864c3ee84a24b1088064162b8dbab8ad5/Makefile#L49-L53\r\n\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?\r\n\r\nInstead of directly installing the latest go modules have them pinned with something like `tools.go` https://github.com/ossf/scorecard/blob/main/tools.go and tools.go could be a separate go module instead of the main module to reduce the scope adding additional dependencies.\r\n\r\nThe make file could have a target like this https://github.com/ossf/scorecard/blob/f55b86d6627cc3717e3a0395e03305e81b9a09be/Makefile#L38 to install the dependencies.\r\n\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature?\r\n\r\nYes, I am willing to implement this.",
